# AT Website Project Rules for Cursor AI

## CRITICAL STYLING RULES
- NEVER use gradient backgrounds - only solid colors
- Match home page styling patterns exactly
- Use Tailwind CSS for most styling, SCSS only for complex components
- Follow established color palette: primary (#2563eb), secondary (#64748b), accent (#f59e0b)

## COMPONENT STRUCTURE (MANDATORY)
All Astro components must follow this exact order:
1. Imports (Astro, React, Vue, etc.)
2. Props interface/type definitions  
3. Data fetching (getStaticPaths, etc.)
4. Component logic
5. HTML structure
6. Tailwind classes
7. Event handlers
8. Accessibility attributes
9. SCSS styles (if needed)

## FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Components: PascalCase.astro (HeroSection.astro)
- Content: _sectionName.js for data, .md for markdown
- Pages: kebab-case.astro (explore-pods.astro)
- Utilities: camelCase.ts (podUtils.ts)

## CONTENT MANAGEMENT
- Home page: Use /content/pod.js for general content
- Pod details: Use /content/pods/{pod_file}.md for detailed information
- Keep content structure consistent across all sections

## TECHNOLOGY STACK
- Framework: Astro 5.12.0
- Styling: Tailwind CSS 3.3.3 + SCSS
- Deployment: Vercel
- Language: TypeScript preferred

## FORBIDDEN PRACTICES
- No gradient backgrounds
- No inline styles
- No components without following mandatory structure
- No skipping TypeScript types
- No ignoring accessibility requirements

## QUALITY REQUIREMENTS
- Responsive design implementation
- Accessibility attributes (aria-labels, alt text, etc.)
- Error handling
- Performance optimization
- TypeScript types for all functions and components

## REFERENCE DOCUMENTATION
- PROJECT_DOCUMENTATION.md - Complete project overview
- DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md - Detailed development rules  
- STYLE_GUIDE.md - Visual design system
- COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md - Component catalog
- QUICK_REFERENCE.md - Daily development guide

Always maintain consistency with existing code patterns and refer to the full documentation files for complete guidelines. 